    public class MicrosoftTeamsLogEventObserver
extends HttpPostJsonLogEventObserver
    Sends log messages to Microsoft Teams through a webhook extension. Must be configured with a .url property as a webhook. See Microsoft documentation on how to get a Webhook url. This observer batches messages as standard for BatchingLogEventObserver, using the idleThreshold, idleThreshold, and cooldownTime to determine when to flush the batch. It support FilteredLogEventObserver properties threshold, suppressMarkers and requireMarker to filter sent messages
